    "answer_id" : 33070602,
    "question_id" : 1456566,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can check for NaN by using <code>var != var</code>. <code>NaN</code> does not equal <code>NaN</code>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>EDIT</strong>: This is probably by far the worst method. It's confusing, terrible for readability, and overall bad practice.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 170737,
      "reputation" : 2393,
      "user_id" : 397677,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/PTYbI.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Grzegorz Gajos",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/397677/grzegorz-gajos"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 22,
    "last_activity_date" : 1467207500,
    "creation_date" : 1467207500,
    "answer_id" : 38101309,
    "question_id" : 1456566,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You might want to consider also checking if a value is finite via <code>Double.isFinite(value)</code>. Since Java 8 there is a new method in <code>Double</code> class where you can check at once if a value is not NaN and infinity.</p>\n\n<pre><code>/**\n * Returns {@code true} if the argument is a finite floating-point\n * value; returns {@code false} otherwise (for NaN and infinity\n * arguments).\n *\n * @param d the {@code double} value to be tested\n * @return {@code true} if the argument is a finite\n * floating-point value, {@code false} otherwise.\n * @since 1.8\n */\npublic static boolean isFinite(double d)\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 3211603,
        "reputation" : 300858,
        "user_id" : 2711488,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/t2hoD.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Holger",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2711488/holger"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1676036303,
      "post_id" : 57587057,
      "comment_id" : 133061583,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "There is never a need to write <code>condition? true: false</code>, as <code>condition</code> is already <code>true</code> when <code>true</code> and <code>false</code> when <code>false</code>. Even shorter is <code>Double.isNaN(dbl)</code> which skips the unnecessary conversion from a <code>double</code> value to a <code>Double</code> object."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1940902,
      "reputation" : 153,
      "user_id" : 1747138,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 25,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/kH7Kz.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Teela",
